# Git Workflow

For all Edtech website changes, follow this branch workflow:

- Start from the latest `main` branch before new work.
- Pull the remote `main` branch before creating a feature branch.
- Create a focused feature branch for each update, using names like `feat/update-home-content` or `fix/contact-form-copy`.
- Make content, design, or code changes only on the feature branch.
- Commit with a conventional commit message such as `feat: update website content`, `fix: correct contact details`, or `docs: update project guide`.
- Push the feature branch and raise a PR/MR into `main`.
- Use squash merge for the PR/MR.
- Delete the source branch after the PR/MR is merged.
- After merge, return to `main`, pull the latest remote changes, and create the next feature branch from the updated `main`.

Use this command pattern when starting new work:

```powershell
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git checkout -b feat/<short-update-name>
```

Use this command pattern when publishing work:

```powershell
git add .
git commit -m "feat: update website content"
git push -u origin feat/<short-update-name>
```
